class Solution:
    def minMoves(self, target: int, maxDoubles: int) -> int:
        moves = 0
        while target > 1:
            if maxDoubles == 0:
                # If no more doubles are allowed, just increment to 1
                return moves + target - 1
            if target % 2 == 0:
                # If target is even, we can use a double operation
                target //= 2
                maxDoubles -= 1
            else:
                # If target is odd, decrement it by 1 to make it even
                target -= 1
            moves += 1
        return moves
```

This solution works by starting from the target and working backwards to 1. It uses the allowed double operations whenever possible (when the target is even) to minimize the number of moves. If the target is odd, it decrements by 1 to make it even. If no more double operations are allowed, it simply increments the remaining difference to reach 1.
